item.title: Help with cheezescape
item.dc:creator: @PussyCrunch PussyCrunch
item.description:
@PussyCrunch wrote:

Simply click start, right-click on “My Computer” then click properties, then click the Advanced tab, then click Enviroment Varibles, and click the top new button.

Where it says Varible name put…

Classpath

And where it says Varible Value put…

CLASSPATH=C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_06\bin;%CLASSPATH%;.

Then click Ok.

Then click new button again. The same one as before. And for Varible name put…

path

And for Varible value put…

C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_06\bin;C:\Program Files\Java\jre1.5.0_06\bin

Note: All your sources file must be in your Java development kits .bin file. Or else when you compile, it will say “javac” is not recognized blah blah when you compile.

These codes were taken from darkest_mage’s tutorial. Credit goes to him for the codes.
